    <prj:ScienceGoal mode="Standard">
        <prj:name>Image q1 Eri debris disk</prj:name>
        <prj:note>The primary goal of the proposed observation is to image continuum emission from the q1Eri debris disk which has an outer radius within 120au (7"). An angular resolution of 0.7" and a continuum sensitivity of 20 microJy/beam will be necessary to ensure differentiation between the 4 different planetary system scenarios discussed in the proposal. The required continuum sensitivity drives our time request, which consists of 1.6hr on-source, and 2.8hr including overheads. Additionally, we will to search for CO J=3-2 line emission within the disk. Taking into account our continuum constraints, we will obtain a line sensitivity which will enable us to probe very low (10^-4Mearth) CO mass levels. The spectral resolution (0.85 km/s) will be adequate to resolve the Keplerian spread in velocities (~8 km/s) that is expected from CO gas within the disk.</prj:note>
